  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "This enables the container to edit the `/etc/resolv.conf` and `/etc/hosts` file without modifying the host's ones (e.g. add the k8s' DNS setting to the hostNetwork container).\n\nThe question here is should we apply the dns options (dns, dns search, dns opt) to the hostnetwork container by default?\n\ncc @quentin-m @kubernetes/sig-rktnetes @kubernetes/sig-network \n",
